The Ohio Academy of Science
August 24, 2018 at 11:41 AM ·

The Ohio Academy of Science selected 61 Ohio schools and 672 teachers to receive The Governor's Thomas Edison Awards for Excellence in STEM Education and Student Research. Congratulations to each of the awardees!

"These schools and teachers push the boundaries of the traditional classroom by advising and mentoring student- originated research and other hands-on experiences", said Michael E. Woytek, CEO, The Ohio Academy of Science

For a complete list of schools and teachers, please see the 2018 Press

http://www.ohiosci.org/s/2018-Edison-Press-release.pdf

Akron Public Schools Athens City School District Holy Trinity Catholic School St. Raphael School - Bay Village Bellbrook Middle School

post_text: On Saturday, March 3, two Dayton High juniors, Ajarae R. and Shayla F. traveled to Indianapolis to compete in the Concept Spoken Word Competition. In January and February, Ajarae and Shayla wrote and submitted their poem on the topic “A Change is Going to Come.” After working for months writing, they took the stage for their first competition. Though they didn’t bring home any of the prizes, they both received overwhelmingly positive feedback from the judges, contest organizers, audience members, and fellow competitors, and they are looking forward to competing again next year! #wearehorizon

post_text: On March 26th, 2018 Horizon Parent Academy started parenting workshops. The first workshop that was held was called Creating a Vision for your Family! Mrs. Kimberly Jarvis from the National Parent Academy presented this workshop and helped parents understand what a vision is and what our purpose is here in this life. The parents created their vision board for their selves and their family. The workshop was very interactive and the parents had a blast! The next parenting workshop will be held on Monday April 16th, 2018. The focus is Helping children manage/resolve conflict reasonably! We hope to see you all there! #wearehorizon

post_text: On Monday January 29th, Horizon Science Academy hosted a community event. The event was focused on development of the Forest Park Area. There were public officials, development directors and coordinators, and residents of Harrison Township present, about 85-90 people altogether. They discussed the area of Forest Park where the development will occur along with ideas for the development area. I heard ideas such as, a community center for our children, sidewalks to make transportation easier for those who walk, restaurants, more natural development around the metro parks, a movie theater, bowling alley, and other recreational ideas for our youth.

post_text:
On Tuesday December 12th, Horizon Science Academy High School hosted a community event. The purpose of the meeting was to discuss a development plan of the Forest Park area. Horizon Science Academy sits almost in the middle of this area, and as a community charter school, we strive to serve our families in our community. Several Harrison Township officials were among the attendees at the meeting. A plan of action was discussed among those in attendance as well as their next steps.
In the next few months, the development committee plans on holding a couple meetings that will be open to the community/public for ideas on how to develop the Forest Park area. These meetings will be held here at Horizon Science Academy and our families are encouraged to attend to have the opportunity for their voice to be heard. I will make sure to keep everyone updated on the upcoming community meetings.

Horizon Science Academy sits almost in the middle of this area, and as a community charter school, we strive to serve our families in our community. Several Harrison Township officials were among the attendees at the meeting. A plan of action was discussed among those in attendance as well as their next steps.
In the next few months, the development committee plans on holding a couple meetings that will be open to the community/public for ideas on how to develop the Forest Park area. These meetings will be held here at Horizon Science Academy and our families are encouraged to attend to have the opportunity for their voice to be heard. I will make sure to keep everyone updated on the upcoming community meetings.

post_text: On Thursday November, 9th we held our first annual Thanksgiving dinner here at Horizon Science Academy. We served turkey, mashed potatoes, gravy, mixed vegetables, corn bread, rolls, and a variety of desserts. There were approximately 75 people in attendance. There was also a turkey give-a-way held at the end of the dinner where 20 turkeys were given to our families. We like to give a special thanks to Meijer department store for providing the turkeys needed for the dinner and the give-a-way. Also, special thanks to Mrs. Florence and her staff for helping to prepare the dinner! Thank you to those who were able to attend! The dinner was a huge success and we look forward to holding one again next year!
